
::::::  AWS Console Sections & Their Use :::::::

1. Compute

ðŸ‘‰ Ye section servers aur applications run karne ke liye hota hai.

EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud): Virtual servers banane ke liye (Linux/Windows).

Lambda: Code ko bina server manage kiye run karne ke liye (serverless).

Elastic Beanstalk: Application deploy karne ka easy tool (auto scaling, load balancer ke sath).

ECS (Elastic Container Service): Docker containers ko manage karne ke liye.

EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service): Kubernetes clusters chalane ke liye.



2. Storage

ðŸ‘‰ Data save karne aur backup ke liye.

S3 (Simple Storage Service): Unlimited object storage (files, images, backups).

EBS (Elastic Block Store): EC2 ke liye hard disk jaisa storage.

EFS (Elastic File System): Shared file system, multiple EC2 ke liye.

Glacier: Cheap storage for backups/archive (long term).


3. Database

ðŸ‘‰ Managed databases ke liye.

RDS (Relational Database Service): MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, SQL Server, Aurora.

DynamoDB: NoSQL database (super fast, scalable).

Redshift: Data warehouse (analytics ke liye).

ElastiCache: Caching (Redis/Memcached).


4. Networking & Content Delivery

ðŸ‘‰ Network aur traffic control ke liye.

VPC (Virtual Private Cloud): Apna private network banane ke liye.

Route 53: DNS aur domain management.

CloudFront: Content delivery network (fast website load globally).

Elastic Load Balancing (ELB): Traffic ko multiple servers me distribute karna.

Direct Connect: AWS ko directly connect karna (high speed link).



5. Security, Identity & Compliance

ðŸ‘‰ Security aur users manage karne ke liye.

IAM (Identity & Access Management): Users, groups, permissions.

Cognito: App users ka authentication (sign-in, sign-up).

KMS (Key Management Service): Data encryption keys manage karne ke liye.

Shield: DDoS protection.

WAF (Web Application Firewall): Web security rules set karne ke liye.



6. DevOps / Developer Tools

ðŸ‘‰ CI/CD aur monitoring ke liye.

CodeCommit: Git repository (GitHub jaisa).

CodeBuild: Source code compile aur build karne ke liye.

CodeDeploy: App ko EC2 ya Lambda pe deploy karna.

CodePipeline: CI/CD pipeline banane ke liye.

CloudWatch: Logs aur metrics monitor karne ke liye.

X-Ray: Application tracing.


7. Management & Governance

ðŸ‘‰ AWS resources ko manage karne ke liye.

CloudFormation: Infrastructure as code (YAML/JSON template se resource create).

CloudTrail: AWS account ke sabhi activity ka record (audit ke liye).

Config: Resources ka configuration track karna.

Organizations: Multiple AWS accounts ko ek sath manage karna.

Trusted Advisor: Best practices aur cost saving suggestions.



8. Machine Learning

ðŸ‘‰ AI aur ML services ke liye.

SageMaker: ML models train aur deploy karne ke liye.

Rekognition: Image & video analysis (face detection).

Polly: Text-to-speech.

Translate: Language translation.

Lex: Chatbot banane ke liye (Alexa jaisa).


9. Analytics

ðŸ‘‰ Data analysis aur processing ke liye.

Athena: Directly S3 me stored data pe SQL queries run karna.

EMR (Elastic MapReduce): Big Data processing (Hadoop, Spark).

Kinesis: Real-time data streaming (like IoT, logs).

QuickSight: Business intelligence dashboards.



10. Migration & Transfer

ðŸ‘‰ Data aur applications ko AWS me migrate karne ke liye.

DMS (Database Migration Service): On-premise database â†’ AWS.

Snowball: Physical device for transferring TBs of data.

DataSync: Fast transfer between on-premise and AWS.



11. Customer Engagement

ðŸ‘‰ Customer ke sath interact karne ke liye.

SES (Simple Email Service): Email sending.

SNS (Simple Notification Service): Notifications (SMS, email, apps).

SQS (Simple Queue Service): Message queues (decouple applications).



12. Cost Management

ðŸ‘‰ AWS kharch track karne ke liye.

Billing Dashboard: Cost check karne ke liye.

Cost Explorer: Cost visualization aur analysis.

Budgets: Alerts set karne ke liye jab cost exceed ho jaye.



